Renovators seeking a project will find inspiration and challenge in this two-bedroom timber home that has retained original features including windows and interior tongue and groove walls. Set on 956m², this property enjoys a prime location within walking distance of the local primary school, town swimming pool, park and town centre. Canny investors will recognise the value as a rental property in the currently tight rental market in Malanda.
The yard is completely fenced has a small shed and there is sufficient carport space for several vehicles; town water and sewerage are connected. An inspection will reveal the possibilities here.

put.description:
It is hard to achieve perfection, but this stunning town residence certainly comes close. Flaunting an array of carefully selected finishes complemented by top quality German fixtures, this private street-facing setting is as ideal for families as it is for discerning professionals.
High-end oak wide-board flooring and 10ft ceilings flow through the expansive entertaining zone which showcases massive cavity glass doors that can be thrown back to seamlessly connect indoors with the private alfresco deck – offering space to relax with friends.
Hosts will love the gourmet kitchen that boasts 2-pac charcoal soft-close Blum cabinetry and premium Bosch appliances including an induction cooktop and integrated dishwasher - with a long Caesarstone breakfast bar and Danish pendant lights, these are ultra-stylish surrounds.
A ground floor master with an exquisite ensuite is a coveted inclusion; three further bedrooms upstairs flanking a spacious retreat add more appeal for families – whilst a chic full bathroom on this level, a downstairs powder room, proper laundry and oversized garage with storage just add to a list of highlights. Grohe tapware throughout, Alape steel enamel basins, plantation shutters and Cavalier Bremworth wool carpet plus zoned ducted heating/cooling – this is a features list that just keeps going, and all this in a sought-after tree-lined street within moments of the station, cafes & shops and close to the beach & quality schools.
For all enquiries please contact Katrina O'Brien 0411 626 394 Hodges Mentone/Chelsea.
put.title: QUALITY, CLASS & DESIGNER LUXURY

It is hard to achieve perfection, but this stunning town residence certainly comes close. Flaunting an array of carefully selected finishes complemented by top quality German fixtures, this private street-facing setting is as ideal for families as it is for discerning professionals.
High-end oak wide-board flooring and 10ft ceilings flow through the expansive entertaining zone which showcases massive cavity glass doors that can be thrown back to seamlessly connect indoors with the private alfresco deck – offering space to relax with friends.
Hosts will love the gourmet kitchen that boasts 2-pac charcoal soft-close Blum cabinetry and premium Bosch appliances including an induction cooktop and integrated dishwasher - with a long Caesarstone breakfast bar and Danish pendant lights, these are ultra-stylish surrounds.
A ground floor master with an exquisite ensuite is a coveted inclusion; three further bedrooms upstairs flanking a spacious retreat add more appeal for families – whilst a chic full bathroom on this level, a downstairs powder room, proper laundry and oversized garage with storage just add to a list of highlights. Grohe tapware throughout, Alape steel enamel basins, plantation shutters and Cavalier Bremworth wool carpet plus zoned ducted heating/cooling – this is a features list that just keeps going, and all this in a sought-after tree-lined street within moments of the station, cafes & shops and close to the beach & quality schools.
For all enquiries please contact Katrina O'Brien 0411 626 394 Hodges Mentone/Chelsea.

put.title: QUALITY, CLASS & DESIGNER LUXURY

put.description:
Hawks property Experts proud to present a premium custom design home with exquisite extras which sparkles and shines throughout. A modern marvel that blends stylish surroundings with comfort and practicality.

Showcasing the light-filled layout centres around the sleek designer kitchen, which boasts 60mm stone benchtops, 900mm appliances, and walk in pantry. Practical open floorplan incorporates a comfortable lounge and an inviting family/meal zone.

Creating a splendid heaven for busy parents, the magnificent master presents an enormous walk-in robe and a stunning EnSuite. Meanwhile, the three remaining bedrooms are all robed and share the luxury bathroom with 40mm stone bench & separate powder room.

First-class finishes are abundant, consisting of high ceilings, soft-close cabinetry, plush carpets, a double garage, landscaping, and an immaculate laundry.

Positioned on a fast-growing Northern Suburb Donnybrook, Its located in Donny brae Estate. Excellent everyday amenities can be easily accessed, including schools, parks, playgrounds. Commuting is also a breeze, courtesy of local bus stops and Donnybrook train Station. Easy Access to Hume Freeway.

Don't miss out as this property will not last long!

For inspections and or any queries, please contact :

Karan Kohli- 0422 151 399
Yashika Kohli- 0450 095 399

All photos are for illustration purposes only.

put.description:
Located on a superb 2196m2 parcel of useable land in a picturesque pocket of Shailer Park, this endearing family home is warm, welcoming & ready to become yours!

Set back on the block for ultimate privacy, there is plenty of useable land both in front of & at the rear of the home, making it adaptable for all kinds of purposes. The man of the house will be kept very happy with a HUGE powered workshop (4x10m approx), a double lock-up garage with internal access and NEW epoxy flooring.

The home itself is of solid brick veneer construction and well maintained by its long term owners. The floorplan is well devised for family life with two spacious living and dining zones, ensuring everyone in the family can enjoy their own personal space. The interior is very well presented albeit more suited to buyers who are keen to put their updating skills to the test and really make it their own.

On entry, you will discover a spacious and inviting lounge and dining area. Perfect for the Winter months, this cosy area is a great spot to relax and take some time out. Moving through to the heart of the home you will discover a spacious casual living & dining zone. At the centre of this area is a very well appointed galley style kitchen with a stainless steel oven & plenty of cupboard & bench space.

There are three generously sized bedrooms, all with built-ins. The master bedroom boasts a walk-in wardrobe, spacious ensuite and quality timber flooring. The floorplan of the home with its two spacious living/dining zones makes it easy to find a nook in which to set up an office zone if desired. There is a second spacious bathroom with a separate toilet which in addition to the ensuite, services the home perfectly.

Outdoors, you will discover an expansive covered entertaining area with a pitched roof allowing additional air flow in Summer. This area overlooks a sublime inground saltwater free-form pool. There is so much room for children and pets to run, to play and to explore all 2196m2 of the grounds.

Your vehicles will be secure in the double lock-up garage with its new epoxy flooring and direct access to the home for ease of unloading. There is plenty of additional off street parking for those with multiple vehicles, a boat, caravan or trailer (or the lot for that matter!).

Other quality features include: A separate laundry room, excellent storage solutions throughout the home, air-conditioning in the master bedroom & living area.

Discover the convenience of living in this prime location in the heart of leafy Shailer Park and in walking distance to the Logan Hyperdome. A choice of quality public and private schools are within a few minutes' drive including St Matthews Primary School, Kimberley Park & Shailer Park State Schools & John Paul College. The M1 is within quick & easy access and the Gold Coast and Brisbane City are both within a half hours drive.

put.description:
If you are looking for an opportunity to retain and subdivide while maintaining a grand old home to renovate and call your own, or are looking to rent out while considering your options, then look no further!
Nestled perfectly at the front edge of the boundary, sits this federation style home that remains in its original condition, yet very well maintained.
This property has the added advantage of a prepared subdivision plan with the potential for a triplex block whilst retaining the existing home at the front.
With a little bit of TLC all that's needed and a property that offers easy ongoing maintenance if you work away, this will suit a wide variety of potential owners.

Key features include:
- Triplex potential (ability to easily retain and subdivide)
- Easy access to Midland, Guildford, Airports and roughly 11km to the city centre
- Front lounge with ceiling fans and split system air-conditioning unit and French door entry
to the large front verandah
- Kitchen/dining with walk-in-pantry and access to the rear study/activity room and patio
- Large master bedroom
- Good sized minor bedroom with split system air-conditioning unit
- 6.2m x 6.2m garage with automatic gate

Bassendean is a well-established suburb situated only 20 minutes from the Perth CBD and just 9km from Midland. It offers all the convenience you can think of such as access to main roads, shops, parks and schools nearby. All of the above and much more make it a great place for your family to settle into with potential for multiple options on a future subdivision.

Rates:
Shire $1663.38 per annum (estimate, incl. ESL)
Water $1010.82 per annum

put.description:
Fantastic corner lot now available in Yalyalup Corner estate. This lot sure won't last long with side access giving you plenty of opportunities for smart design to ensure good use of land space.

Introducing - The Bluegum Modern a striking, modern impression of the timeless homestead design.

Featuring high raking ceilings the full length of the living room area, creating a greater sense of space and light throughout the open plan living area.

The expansive kitchen and scullery space flow directly to the dining and alfresco area, perfect for year round entertaining.

The minor three bedrooms sit at one side of the home, alongside a large bathroom and laundry space.

Whilst the grand master retreat sits privately to the other side, featuring a corner retreat, walk in robe and ensuite.

Live Large Down South at Yalyalup Corner
▪ Bigger blocks sizes to fit more life in
▪ Surrounded by an abundance of natural beauty
▪ Georgiana Molloy Anglican School within walking distance
▪ Under 5 mins drive from Busselton town centre
▪ Close to Busselton Margaret River Regional Airport
▪ Fencing & Landscaping Voucher
▪ Attractive estate with cohesive Design Guidelines
▪ NBN Ready
▪ Infill development amongst well-established community, parks and playgrounds
▪ Close to world-class beaches, wineries and year-round events
▪ Just 30 mins drive to Bunbury

If your looking at getting into a home of your own in 2023 then reach out now for more information on 0402 163 601.

Inclusions
- Built by local qualified & experienced trades people
- 20mm Stone benchtops to kitchen
- Luxury Westinghouse 900mm kitchen appliances
- Hob-less showers, with semi frameless pivot door and screen (where shown)
- Double bowl kitchen sink
- Choice of impressive elevations options*
- Soft close draws through out
- Soft Close Cupboards through out
- 6 Star rated Rheem 26L continuous flow hot water system
- Alder tapware and accessories to bathroom, ensuite & toilets
- Chrome floor wastes to all wet areas
- Wide choice of pavers to Verandas, Porchs, and Alfresco areas
- Double clay brick construction* (where shown)
- Gainsborough Tri-Lock entry set to entry door

- Lifetime structural warranty*
